  "prompt": "Can you drink water during exercise? I mean in between sets?",
  "response": "Yes, absolutely! Staying hydrated during exercise is important. Here are some key points about drinking water during workouts:\n\n1. It's recommended to drink water:\n- Between sets\n- During breaks\n- When you feel thirsty\n\n2. Benefits of drinking water during exercise:\n- Prevents dehydration\n- Helps regulate body temperature\n- Maintains performance\n- Reduces fatigue\n\n3. General guidelines:\n- Drink small amounts regularly\n- Don't wait until you're extremely thirsty\n- Aim for about 7-10 ounces every 10-20 minutes during exercise\n\n4. Type of exercise matters:\n- Longer/more intense workouts require more hydration\n- In very hot conditions, you'll need more water\n\n5. Avoid:\n- Drinking too much water at once\n- Drinking only when you feel exhausted\n\nRemember, individual hydration needs vary based on body weight, exercise intensity, and environmental conditions. Listen to your body and drink when you feel the need.",
